author: COMSOL
description: This example uses the Battery with Binary Electrolyte interface for studying the discharge of a zinc-silver oxide battery. The electrochemical reactions in the positive and negative electrodes lead to changes in porosity and species concentration in the electrodes. The geometry is in one dimension and the model is isothermal.
